io.tenmax.poppy

Interface DataFrame

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<DataRow>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RandomAccessDataFrame
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AggregateDataFrame, BaseDataFrame, CacheDataFrame, DistinctDataFrame, FilterDataFrame, PeekDataFrame, ProjectDataFrame, SortDataFrame, SourceDataFrame

    public interface DataFrame
extends java.lang.Iterable<DataRow>
    DataFrame is a sequence of schema-defined rows. The following example illustrates how to use the DataFrame: 
    
 List<Student> students = ...;

 DataFrame.from(students, Student.class)
          .groupby("grade", "room")
          .aggregate(
              avgLong("weight").as("weight"),
              avgLong("height").as("height"))
          .sort("grade", "room")
          .print();
    Just like Stream, it iterates through a data source with as little memory as possible. This allows you processing billion of data with only constant memory. DataFrame provides operations which SQL provides. For example projection, ,filtering, grouping, and aggregation, soring. These operations make it possible to write your own SQL-like statements in your application. In the above example, it is equivalent to 
    
     select
         grade,
         room,
         avg(weight) as weight,
         avg(height) as height
     from Student
     group by grade, room
     order by grade, room
